TY  - JOUR
T1  - Capacity Expansion with Two Producing Regions and Concave Costs
AU  - Fong, C. O.
AU  - Rao, M. R.
Y1  - 1975/11/01
PY  - 1975
DA  - 1975/11/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.22.3.331
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.22.3.331
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 331
EP  - 339
VL  - 22
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A deterministic capacity expansion and shipment planning problem is considered for a single commodity that can be produced in two regions. Demand in each region is nondecreasing over a finite time horizon. Demand in a region in a time period must be satisfied, either by the current production capacity there or by a shipment from the other region. Capacity expansion and shipment costs are assumed to be concave and no inventory of stock is allowed. The problem is to find a schedule of capacity expansion in each region and a schedule of shipment between the two regions, such that the total cost over the time horizon is minimized. To solve this problem a dynamic programming algorithm is devised that is more efficient than known conventional procedures.
AB  - A deterministic capacity expansion and shipment planning problem is considered for a single commodity that can be produced in two regions. Demand in each region is nondecreasing over a finite time horizon. Demand in a region in a time period must be satisfied, either by the current production capacity there or by a shipment from the other region. Capacity expansion and shipment costs are assumed to be concave and no inventory of stock is allowed. The problem is to find a schedule of capacity expansion in each region and a schedule of shipment between the two regions, such that the total cost over the time horizon is minimized. To solve this problem a dynamic programming algorithm is devised that is more efficient than known conventional procedures.
